Sentencas: La2NiO4+delta powders were synthesized using a polyaminocarboxylate complex precursor method.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of La2NiO4+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: La2NiO4+delta electrodes were prepared on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) substrates using a screen-printing technique.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of La2NiO4+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microstructure feature and electrocatalytic activity of the electrodes were investigated with respect to the calcination temperature of the starting powders and sintering temperature of the electrodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of La2NiO4+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of microstructure features on the electrochemical properties of La2NiO4+delta., electrodes have been inspected.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of La2NiO4+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the electrochemical performance of the La2NiO4+delta cathode has been evaluated based on a Ni-SDC anode supported single cell.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of La2NiO4+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cell showed a modified electrochemical performance compared with the literature results, attaining a maximum power density of 295 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of La2NiO4+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For the single cell, applying an Au layer onto the La2NiO4+delta cathode led to an evident reduction of ohmic resistance and a substantial enhancement of the maximum power density to 464 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Electrochemical evaluation of La2NiO4+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
